race.comment: COOL NANCZYE (11) was lining up for the second time and was ridden with more aggression last start, resulting in a close second over 1200m at Forbes. Should have no trouble with the extra 100m and with a little further progress can break the ice this afternoon. NORTOKO (10) gave up an early lead and failed to recover when last at the races 39 days ago over 1600m at Queanbeyan. Returned comparatively good figures in his two runs last prep in the 1350m-1400m range. This looks a nice race for him. HUTT STREET (2) raced handy then dug deep under pressure to finish less than a length away over this distance at Dubbo recently. Won't find this as tough so a long-awaited maiden win is on the cards. SPIRIT OF SAINTLY (5) is a 25-start maiden whose latest effort at Dubbo was solid - each-way contender on that form.
